---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Testimonials & Reviews for Yoga Studios — SocialProof" description="Fill more classes. Retain more students. Collect real testimonials from your yoga community and display them on your studio's website — free for one widget." canonical="https://socialproof.dev/for/yoga-studios">
<style>

    .hero { padding: 80px 24px 56px; text-align: center; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; color: #111; margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .hero p { font-size: 1.25rem; color: #555; margin-bottom: 36px; }
    .hero .cta-group { display: flex; gap: 14px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .why-section { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 60px 24px; }
    .why-section h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 16px; text-align: center; }
    .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 28px; margin-top: 40px; }
    .why-card { background: #f9f9f9; border-radius: 12px; padding: 28px; }
    .why-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .why-card p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.6; }
    .own-your-reviews { background: #f0fdf4; padding: 60px 24px; }
    .own-inner { max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .own-inner h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .own-inner p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .quote-section { max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 60px 24px; text-align: center; }
    .quote-section blockquote { font-size: 1.3rem; font-style: italic; color: #333; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .quote-section cite { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #888; }
    .cta-section { background: #111; color: #fff; padding: 60px 24px; text-align: center; }
    .cta-section h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .cta-section p { font-size: 1.1rem; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; }
    .btn-primary { background: #6c47ff; color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; }
    .btn-secondary { background: transparent; color: #111; border: 1.5px solid #ccc; padding: 13px 28px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; }
    .btn-white { background: #fff; color: #111; padding: 14px 28px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; }
    nav { border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; padding: 16px 24px; }
    .nav-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; }
    .logo { font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.2rem; text-decoration: none; color: #111; }
    .nav-links { display: flex; gap: 24px; align-items: center; }
    .nav-links a { text-decoration: none; color: #555; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .btn-nav { background: #6c47ff; color: #fff !important; padding: 8px 18px; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 600; }
    footer { border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding: 32px 24px; text-align: center; }
    footer a { color: #888; font-size: 0.9rem; text-decoration: none; margin: 0 12px; }
    .steps-section { max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 60px 24px; }
    .steps-section h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 40px; text-align: center; }
    .step { display: flex; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 32px; align-items: flex-start; }
    .step-num { background: #6c47ff; color: #fff; border-radius: 50%; width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .step-content h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .step-content p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.6; }
    .faq-section { max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 60px 24px; }
    .faq-section h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 40px; text-align: center; }
    .faq-item { margin-bottom: 28px; }
    .faq-item h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .faq-item p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.6; }
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
      .cta-group { flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
    }
</style>

<nav>
  <div class="nav-inner">
    <a href="/" class="logo">SocialProof</a>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/for/fitness-studios">Fitness</a>
      <a href="/for/restaurants">Restaurants</a>
      <a href="/for/salons">Salons</a>
      <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-nav">Start free</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <h1>Your students' words fill your classes.</h1>
  <p>Yoga studios thrive on community and word-of-mouth. SocialProof helps you collect authentic testimonials from students and display them on your site — so the next person searching for a studio sees real stories, not just a star rating.</p>
  <div class="cta-group">
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-primary">Start free — no credit card</a>
    <a href="/for/fitness-studios" class="btn-secondary">See fitness studio page</a>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="why-section">
  <h2>Why yoga studios use SocialProof</h2>
  <div class="why-grid">
    <div class="why-card">
      <h3>Fill classes, not seats</h3>
      <p>A new student deciding between studios will choose the one where real people share what changed for them — not just the one with the most Google stars. Testimonials on your site convert.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card">
      <h3>Teacher training social proof</h3>
      <p>If you run a YTT program, testimonials from graduates are your most powerful marketing. Collect them automatically and display them where prospective students are making their decision.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card">
      <h3>Community feel, not corporate reviews</h3>
      <p>Google and Yelp give you star ratings. SocialProof gives you stories — the student who found her breath again, the teacher who finally committed to his practice. That's what builds a studio.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card">
      <h3>No awkward ask required</h3>
      <p>Send your collection link after a workshop, a 30-day challenge, or a teacher training. Students click, write a few sentences, and submit. You didn't have to beg or follow up.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card">
      <h3>Own what your students say</h3>
      <p>A Google review lives on Google. A testimonial you collect lives on your site, in your words section, wherever you need it. Platform changes don't erase five years of community voice.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-card">
      <h3>Embed anywhere in minutes</h3>
      <p>Drop a single line of code on your website — WordPress, Squarespace, Webflow, or custom-built. Your testimonials appear exactly where you need them, styled to match your studio.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="steps-section">
  <h2>How it works for yoga studios</h2>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h3>Sign up and get your collection link</h3>
      <p>Create a free account in 30 seconds. You immediately get a unique link students can use to submit a testimonial — no app download, no login required on their end.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h3>Share it with your community</h3>
      <p>Drop the link in your studio newsletter, your post-class email, your Instagram bio, or your WhatsApp community group. Students tap and write — it takes them two minutes.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h3>Approve and display</h3>
      <p>Testimonials land in your dashboard. Review, approve, and publish. Add them to your homepage, your class schedule page, your YTT page — wherever a potential student is reading.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="own-your-reviews">
  <div class="own-inner">
    <h2>The Google review problem</h2>
    <p>Google reviews are great for discovery — when someone searches "yoga studio near me" and your rating shows. But they're out of your control, they can disappear, and they don't go <em>on your site</em>.</p>
    <p>SocialProof sits alongside Google, not instead of it. You still want those stars. But when someone lands on your homepage, your schedule page, your teacher training page — that's where student stories in your own space convert browsers to members.</p>
    <p>Free forever for one widget. No credit card required.</p>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top: 8px; display: inline-block;">Try it free</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="quote-section">
  <blockquote>"I sent the link to everyone who finished our 200-hour YTT. Within a week I had 12 testimonials on the program page. Enrollment for the next cohort filled faster than ever."</blockquote>
  <cite>— Studio owner, Austin TX</cite>
</section>

<section class="faq-section">
  <h2>Questions from studio owners</h2>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>How do students submit a testimonial?</h3>
    <p>You send them a link. They click it, type a short testimonial, and hit submit. No account required, no app to install. It works on any phone or laptop.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Can I use this for my teacher training program specifically?</h3>
    <p>Yes. You can collect as many testimonials as you want on the free plan. Use the same collection link for all programs, or create multiple widgets to display YTT testimonials separately from general class testimonials on the Pro plan.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>What does "free forever" actually mean?</h3>
    <p>You get one active widget — a testimonial display you can embed on your site — completely free, no time limit. Collect unlimited testimonials, display them in one place. Pro ($9/month) unlocks multiple widgets for different pages or programs.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Will it work with my Squarespace or WordPress site?</h3>
    <p>Yes. You paste one line of code anywhere on your site. It works with Squarespace, WordPress, Webflow, Wix, or any custom-built site.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>What about Google reviews — should I still ask for those?</h3>
    <p>Absolutely. SocialProof doesn't replace Google reviews — it complements them. Google reviews help people find you; SocialProof testimonials help people decide once they've found you.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
  <h2>Start collecting testimonials today</h2>
  <p>Free forever for one widget. No credit card. Takes 30 seconds to set up.</p>
  <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-white">Start free — try it now</a>
</section>

<footer>
  <a href="/">Home</a>
  <a href="/for/fitness-studios">Fitness Studios</a>
  <a href="/for/restaurants">Restaurants</a>
  <a href="/for/salons">Salons</a>
  <a href="/for/coaches">Coaches</a>
